a manhattan jury has added millions of dollars in damages to those awarded in the death of a woman killed by police officers firing at an armed bank robber who was using her as a human shield in july 1999 a jury awarded 57 million later reduced to 4 million to the family of aurea bonnie vargas 41 who was killed in 1993 when the robber took her hostage on riverside drive the robber was also killed the 1999 jury ruled that the six officers who fired 29 shots had acted negligently on friday another manhattan jury ruled that the police had acted with reckless disregard a more serious charge and awarded a further 3 million in damages to ms vargas 's estate and 1 million to her brother ramon santiago who witnessed the shooting the city did not appeal the first verdict but lawyers for the city say they will appeal this one ian urbina nyt

